{"id": 223747322, "title": "The responsibility was doubled by representing Emirati football in the Club World Cup", "text": "The Board of Directors of Al Ain Club Investment Company congratulated the wise leadership on the occasion of the Al Ain Club team winning the AFC Champions League title for the second time in its history after its victory yesterday over the Japanese Yokohama Marinos team 5-1 in the second leg of the final. Mohammed bin Thaloub Al Darei, Chairman of the Board of Directors, said that Al Ain Club is on the cusp of an important stage to represent Emirati football in the 2025 FIFA Club World Championship with its new system with the participation of \u201c32\u201d teams in the United States, in addition to large and long-established clubs, most notably England\u2019s Manchester City, Spain\u2019s Real Madrid, and Bayern. Germany\u2019s Munich, Italy\u2019s Juventus, France\u2019s Paris Saint-Germain, England\u2019s Chelsea and other qualified clubs. Al Ain Club is the last qualifier from Arab countries for the Club World Cup in its new format, which will start in the summer of 2025. He pointed out that Al Ain Club\u2019s honorable achievement in the AFC Champions League culminates in the care and attention of the country\u2019s wise leadership for sports and athletes, in addition to the great moral support from the Emirati fans and Al Ain Club fans for the players during the team\u2019s journey in the current stage of the Asian Championship. He appreciated the great role of the players and the technical and administrative staff for demonstrating the good technical level and overcoming the obstacle of the Japanese team with determination and responsibility, to reach the second title with all merit and ability, so that the Al Ain team confirms once again in this tournament its ability to achieve victories and overcome all challenges to reach the podium and raise the flag of the UAE. On the podium.", "summary": "<p>The Board of Directors of Al Ain Cl